$ Private SQL area: run-time area
@ run-time area

The *run-time area* is part of the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA/private-SQL-area.

The *run-time area* stores information that is needed to → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/execution[execute an SQL Statement] such as the number of records that were already fetched.

The amount in bytes for the run-time area can be queried from the column `RUNTIME_MEM` in → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/sql/diff-sql_sqlarea[`V$SQL` and `V$SQLAREA`].
